OL,3,CCalls for cervical screening public
OL,4,Cinquiry as 'patience is wearing thin'
OL,6,F"No-one has taken accountability for
OL,7,Fthe scandal that happened over 13
OL,8,Fyears and, as a group, we still have
OL,9,Fmany questions that remain unanswered
OL,10,F` how did this happen, why did it
OL,11,Fcontinue for 13 years and who is going
OL,12,Fto take responsibility?"
OL,14,FMr McGarrity added: "Ladies with
OL,15,FLetters has engaged with the Minister
OL,16,Ffor Health on these issues for over a
OL,17,Fyear.
OL,19,F"They have waited long enough, and
OL,20,Ftheir patience is wearing thin.
